her than the rich of the mid-ages. The poor of today have access to antibiotics, electricity, smart-phones, an abundance of food, clean drinking water, etc.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":890},"end":{"line":18,"column":250,"offset":1139},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":890},"end":{"line":18,"column":250,"offset":1139},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The rich of the mid-ages did not (all) have this. This is due to wealth creation, and technology is the multiplier behind this. Wealth creation enlarges accessibility and availability to all kinds of people.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":1143},"end":{"line":20,"column":208,"offset":1350},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":1143},"end":{"line":20,"column":208,"offset":1350},"indent":[]}},{"type":"blockquote","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Capitalism, meaning free markets, is intrinsic to the human species","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":3,"offset":1356},"end":{"line":22,"column":70,"offset":1423},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":3,"offset":1356},"end":{"line":22,"column":70,"offset":1423},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","value":"<cite>","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":3,"offset":1430},"end":{"line":24,"column":9,"offset":1436},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":"Naval","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":9,"offset":1436},"end":{"line":24,"column":14,"offset":1441},"indent":[]}},{"type":"html","value":"</cite>","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":14,"offset":1441},"end":{"line":24,"column":21,"offset":1448},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":3,"offset":1430},"end":{"line":24,"column":21,"offset":1448},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1,"offset":1354},"end":{"line":24,"column":21,"offset":1448},"indent":[1,1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Since the dawn of time, we've exchanged information with each other and have always kept track of this information in forms of credits and debits. If you worked for someone, you will keep track of your credits and debits.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1,"offset":1452},"end":{"line":26,"column":222,"offset":1673},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1,"offset":1452},"end":{"line":26,"column":222,"offset":1673},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"What lets the human species cooperate? It is because we can keep track of credits and debits. We ask ourselves: who put in how much work? Who contributed how much? That is all a ","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1,"offset":1677},"end":{"line":28,"column":179,"offset":1855},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"free market capitalism","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":181,"offset":1857},"end":{"line":28,"column":203,"offset":1879},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":179,"offset":1855},"end":{"line":28,"column":205,"offset":1881},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" is.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":205,"offset":1881},"end":{"line":28,"column":209,"offset":1885},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1,"offset":1677},"end":{"line":28,"column":209,"offset":1885},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"We need free minds and free markets. Voluntary small-scale exchanges between humans that won't negatively impact others.","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1,"offset":1889},"end":{"line":30,"column":121,"offset":2009},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1,"offset":1889},"end":{"line":30,"column":121,"offset":2009},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Wealth creation is not about taking. It's about creating abundance in this world.","position":{"start":{"l